When the spiritual agrees with a being, the physical undoubtedly follows suit. Indeed, for the Social Democratic Party (SDP) presidential candidate, Prince Adewole Adebayo, the spiritual side of his presidential ambition has been signed, sealed and delivered. This follows his recent endorsement by world acclaimed Yoga Guru, Gurudev Sri Sri Ravi Shankar and several good friends during a visit to the Art of Living Centre in Washington DC, USA. Typical of great leaders, Adebayo and Gurudev Sri Sri Ravi Shankar expressed admiration for each other’s work and commitment to public happiness and global peace. Particularly, Adebayo commended Gurudev for his lifetime of work towards the advancement of the spiritual growth of the human race, global peace through universal happiness and commitment to one humanity for all, while also inviting him to pray for peace and happiness in Nigeria and among her leaders. Accompanied on the visit by his campaign strategist, Washington’s legendary Ms Jan Du- Plain, Dr Ralph Bello-Fadile, Special Advisor, Dr KY Dele, Senior Special Assistant, presidential photo-historian Patrician McDougall and Special Assistant Mr Salewa Ladipo, Adebayo laid out his vision for Nigeria, a country that is a paradise for her own people, a pride of the black people globally and a blessing to the world, noting that Nigeria will not only prosper materially having been blessed with all it takes to overcome want and deprivations but to thrive and attain the peak of material success. In response, Guredev expressed gratitude for the visit of the presidential candidate and admired his commitment to the peace, happiness and prosperity of Nigeria, adding that the friendship and visit are not a coincidence but divinely ordained, noting that just like Adebayo, it was from his childhood days he dreamed of his leadership role and global place in the world today. The Guru dressed and honoured Adebayo and his team in a brief ceremony, prayed for Nigeria and directly addressed the Nigerian people in a short message, while also announcing his plan to visit the country in